Description: Here is a Kay Electric Archtop that I’ve had a few years. It sounds about like you’d expect it to sound. Plays about how you’d expect it to play. It’s seen a lot of stuff, but considering how old it is? It’s in decent shape! All wear is cosmetic. Seems like most of the wear is from where someone tied a strap on the headstock. The binding is in surprisingly good shape with all of it intact. There’s some wear around the butt of the guitar, where the strap peg is, as well as on the top of the head stock. The pickguard has a crack at the screw that holds it in place, but it’s pretty secure. The action is a touch high but not that bad- prolly needs a good setup to be a good player. Would be killer for slide guitar. Doesn’t stay in tune perfectly, but again, with a little bit of work? It would be a dandy player. The electronics all work well. Has a great grit to it when plugged in. I have not heard it crackle or anything like that. When unplugged, has a biggish sound to it. If you’re looking for that Jack White whiskey soaked grit (insert any other cliche catchphrase) sound... this is your guitar. If you’re looking to play some James Taylor... this ain’t your girl. If you’re looking at this guitar, you know what you’re looking for. The serial number is “L2581” for those of you that want to date it. I love the headstock of this thing. Auction is starting at a penny, with no reserve. Shipping is $50 domestic, because I want to drop this thing off at the ups store and have them pack it and all that. I’ll send you a shipping number. International? I have no idea- call it $150? I could lose bad on that because I haven’t checked out the prices in a while, but that number sounds good. If it’s too much message me and I’ll change it. Live in Kentucky and want to pick this thing up? I’ll meet you at Clamato’s on Versailles Rd, buy you food, and bullshit with you over dinner, so that I don’t have to go to the UPS store. After all, doesn’t like good Mexican food? I don’t know if I have a gig bag laying around for this thing or not. If I have an extra, I’ll throw it in too. Don’t bid on this expecting that tho. PayPal only.
Title: VINTAGE KAY ARCHTOP HOLLOWBODY ELECTRIC GUITAR

Charity.Mission: Operation Blazing Sword is a grass-roots organization dedicated to help queer people learn how to defend themselves by teaching them firearm safety and operation by pairing them with queer-friendly gun owners who will teach them without prejudice. When this happens they each see the other not as political enemies, but as fellow human beings whose lives have value.
